      "OTC supplement. **Physta extract is the gold standard** — branded ingredient by the Malaysian Forest Research Institute (Forest Research Institute Malaysia / FRIM), used in most clinical trials. Brands using Physta: Double Wood, Nootropics Depot, Real Mushrooms, Bulletproof, Thorne Tongkat Ali. Generic 'Tongkat Ali extract' without Physta or eurycomanone standardization is variable in potency. '100:1' and '200:1' ratio products may be reasonable but verify eurycomanone content if possible. **Authenticity concern**: Tongkat Ali roots are sourced from old-growth Eurycoma longifolia plants (typically 5–10+ years old for adequate eurycomanone content) — sustainable sourcing is genuinely a concern as wild populations face harvest pressure.",
    notes:
      "## Beginner Protocol\nPhysta 200mg/day AM × 1 week, then 400mg/day AM × 8 weeks. Track: morning erections, libido, energy, mood, body composition. Bracket with hormone panel (total T, free T, SHBG, LH, FSH, estradiol, cortisol if available) at baseline and 8 weeks. Effects on labs are modest — free T and T:cortisol ratio more consistent than total T elevation.\n\n## Advanced Protocol\nT-support stack: Tongkat Ali 400mg + Cistanche 600mg + Fadogia Agrestis 600mg (the Huberman protocol). Cycle 8 weeks on / 2 weeks off. Add boron 6mg/day for free-T support, magnesium glycinate 400mg PM for HPA axis + sleep, vitamin D3 5000 IU + zinc 25mg as foundational micronutrient support. The stack works best for stress-related or age-related modest T decline; men with frank hypogonadism need TRT, not herbal stacks.\n\nFor users on TRT wanting additional free-T support: Tongkat Ali 200–400mg can layer onto TRT to address SHBG-bound T fraction. Coordinate with prescriber; monitor labs to prevent supraphysiological free-T.\n\n## Clinical Trial Citations Worth Knowing\nTalbott 2013 (n=63 stressed adults, 200mg Physta/day × 4 weeks): T elevation 16%, cortisol reduction 32%, T:C ratio improved 100%, profile of mood states improved across all subscales. Henkel 2014 (n=109 active middle-aged men, 600mg/day Physta × 12 weeks): significant improvements in T, free T, dehydroepiandrosterone, vigor, fatigue. Tambi 2012 (n=75 idiopathic infertility men, 200mg Physta/day × 3 months): semen quality improvements with 11/75 partner pregnancies. Ismail 2012 (n=109 sub-fertile men, 200mg/day): sperm motility, count improvements. George 2014 (n=63 age-related declining men, 200mg/day × 12 weeks): T-related symptoms improved.\n\n## Reconstitution + Administration\nN/A — oral capsule. AM dosing for most users (some find PM stimulating).\n\n## Synergies\n**Cistanche:** primary stack partner — complementary mechanisms (Tongkat = SHBG modulation; Cistanche = Leydig support). **Fadogia Agrestis:** the third Huberman-protocol component (with cycling caution). **Ashwagandha:** HPA-axis complement, particularly for stress-related low T. **Boron:** free-T fraction support via SHBG and other mechanisms. **Vitamin D3 + Zinc:** foundational micronutrient layer.\n\n## Evidence Quality\nMost-evidence-supported herbal T-support compound. Multiple RCTs in stressed men, older men, and fertility contexts. Physta extract specifically has the largest clinical database. Effect sizes modest but consistent. The 12-week safety data extends to 12 months in some long-term trials.\n\n## Research vs Anecdote\nResearch: solid evidence for SHBG modulation, T:C ratio improvement, libido and mood benefits, sperm parameter improvements; less consistent on absolute total T elevation. Anecdote: positive for stress-related or age-related modest T decline; less impressive in already-optimized users. Decision frame: foundational T-support adaptogen; useful adjunct in comprehensive T-support stacks; not a substitute for TRT in diagnosed hypogonadism.",
